HEADWORD: Sashery
<hw>Sash"er*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From 1st
<er>Sash</er>.]</ety> <def>A collection of sashes; ornamentation by
means of sashes.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Distinguished by their <qex>sasheries</qex> and insignia.</q>
<rj><qau>Carlyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sashoon</ent>⟦br⟧
